<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="584" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1159,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">
This family is represented in the Neotropics by three genera and over 62 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Vilarino, A. &amp; Bispo, P. C." box="[1117,1391,1159,1185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" pagination="386 - 400" refId="ref7067" refString="Vilarino, A. &amp; Bispo, P. C. (2020). New records and two new species of Xiphocentron Brauer 1870 (Trichoptera, Xiphocentronidae) from southern Atlantic Forest, Brazil. Zootaxa, 4851 (2), 386 - 400. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4851.2.11" type="journal article" year="2020">Vilarino &amp; Bispo 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[151,243,1195,1221]" name="Panama" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">Panama</collectingCountry>
, all three Neotropical genera are known: (
<taxonomicName authority="Schmid 1982" authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[709,1024,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Caenocentron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[709,867,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">Caenocentron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schmid, F." box="[873,1024,1195,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref6761" refString="Schmid, F. (1982) La famille des Xiphocentronides (Trichoptera: Annulipalpia). Memoires de la Societe Entomologique du Canada, 121, 1 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 114122 fv" type="journal article" year="1982">Schmid 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmid 1982" authorityName="Schmid" authorityYear="1982" box="[1034,1385,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Machairocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1034,1228,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">Machairocentron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schmid, F." box="[1235,1385,1195,1221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" pagination="1 - 126" refId="ref6761" refString="Schmid, F. (1982) La famille des Xiphocentronides (Trichoptera: Annulipalpia). Memoires de la Societe Entomologique du Canada, 121, 1 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / entm 114122 fv" type="journal article" year="1982">Schmid 1982</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Brauer 1870" authorityName="Brauer" authorityYear="1870" box="[151,453,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Xiphocentronidae" genus="Xiphocentron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,302,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="584">Xiphocentron</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brauer, F. M." box="[310,453,1231,1257]" pageId="6" pageNumber="584" pagination="66" refId="ref5107" refString="Brauer, F. M. (1870) Uber Xiphocentron, eine neue Hydropsychidengattung. Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 20, 66." type="journal article" year="1870">Brauer 1870</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), within which are distributed eight species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
